Business Brief -- Lillian Vernon Corp.:
   Fiscal Third-Quarter Profit
   Jumped 31% to $7.6 Million
Net for the nine months fell 16% to $6.3 million, or 67
cents a share, from $7.5 million, or 81 cents a share, a year
earlier. Sales rose 3.9% to $117 million from $112.6 million.
The company cited higher expenses, including a large increase
in postal rates, for the profit decline.
   Lillian Vernon shares closed yesterday at $15.375, up 37.5
cents, in trading on the American Stock Exchange.